						<summary>

						<p>The writing of the inscription seems to be of about the 11th century A.D. This is built in at the beginning. It seems to record an agreement given by a servant of the temple of Gōvindapāḍi-Perumānaḍigaḷ undertaking to supply 4 <hi rend="italic">nāḻi</hi> of rice daily to the temple (for offerings) as interest on 45 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold received by him from Chandrabhūti-Chaturvēdi-Sōmayāji, a resident of Kōṭṭūr in Mērpaṅgā-nāḍu a division of Maṇaiyiṟkōṭṭam.</p>						

						</summary>
